This example generates a gas cloud which follows a Hernquist profile
and tests whether the tidal tensor (and tidal softening) 
of these particles matches the expected profile. 
Requires swiftsimio (tested with v12.1.3)

(Default Hernquist profile paramters:
  total mass M: 1e10  [Msun]
  characterstic radius a: 10    [kpc]
  particle resolution mres: 1e5 [Msun]
)

Configure with:

./configure --disable-hand-vec --with-kernel=wendland-C2 --with-adaptive-softening=tidal --enable-gravitational-tidal-tensors=yes

Then run run.sh


